{
  "title": "Voice",
  "description": "A live playback instance in the audio graph with a control surface. A Voice is created by playing a Playable via AudioManager.play (and, later, by opening an `AudioInput`). Each `play()` returns an independent Voice, so overlapping concurrent playback of the same asset is just multiple Voices. Concrete voices mix in the capability interfaces (Seekable, Pausable, Loopable, RatePitched, Spatializable) for whatever their backing Web Audio node actually supports — narrow with a capability check (`'seek' in voice`) before using one.",
